{"type":"message","id":"9cc5ccb6","parentId":"378592c9","timestamp":"2026-02-18T18:05:49.729Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Analyzing User Requests**\n\nI'm currently focused on the user's instructions, specifically parsing the multi-step requests. I've begun to outline the tasks, starting with the terminal observer script. My next step is understanding the specific requirements for tailing the logs.\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"write_1771437940675_24","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"import time\nimport os\n\nLOG_FILE = \"logs/bot.log\"\nALERT_FILE = \"logs/live_alerts.log\"\n\ndef tail_log():\n    # Ensure log file exists\n    if not os.path.exists(LOG_FILE):\n        with open(LOG_FILE, 'w') as f:\n            f.write(\"--- Log started ---\\n\")\n            \n    with open(LOG_FILE, \"r\") as f:\n        f.seek(0, 2)  # Go to the end of the file\n        while True:\n            line = f.readline()\n            if not line:\n                time.sleep(0.1)\n                continue\n            \n            # Process line\n            if \"ERROR\" in line or \"CRITICAL\" in line:\n                with open(ALERT_FILE, \"a\") as af:\n                    af.write(line)\n            \n            if \"Trade\" in line:\n                # Simulated Telegram Alert\n                print(f\"SIMULATED TELEGRAM ALERT: {line.strip()}\")\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    # Ensure logs directory exists\n    if not os.path.exists(\"logs\"):\n        os.makedirs(\"logs\")\n    \n    print(\"Starting Live Logger...\")\n    tail_log()\n","file_path":"scripts/live_logger.py","path":"scripts/live_logger.py"},"thoughtSignature":""},{"type":"toolCall","id":"exec_1771437949468_25","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"dir scripts"}},{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Structuring the Workflow**\n\nI've got the task breakdown laid out now. Next, I'm thinking about the control flow: how the terminal observer will interact with the logging and alerting mechanisms. I'll need to figure out how to efficiently tail the log file and filter the output.\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"read_1771437949721_26","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"scripts/broadcast_log.py","path":"scripts/broadcast_log.py"}}],"api":"google-vertex","provider":"google-vertex","model":"gemini-3-pro-preview","usage":{"input":4745,"output":438,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":5183,"cost":{"input":0.00949,"output":0.005256,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.014746}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771437916375}}
